## ClawForge Tools Available

ClawForge is active on this project. The following tools are available to Claude Code:

### Browser Control
- `browser_open <url>` — Navigate to a URL
- `browser_screenshot` — Capture the current page
- `browser_click <selector>` — Click an element
- `browser_type <selector> <text>` — Type into an input
- `browser_evaluate <script>` — Execute JavaScript
- `browser_content` — Extract readable page text

### Persistent Memory
- `memory_search <query>` — Search past observations (vector search)
- `memory_timeline <id>` — Get context around an observation
- `memory_get_observations <ids>` — Retrieve full observation details
- `memory_store <type> <title> <content>` — Manually save to memory
- `memory_context` — Inject recent session context (auto-called on start)

### Web Search
- `web_search <query>` — DuckDuckGo search
- `web_fetch <url>` — Fetch and extract readable page content

### Design Preview
- `design_preview <html>` — Render HTML/CSS in browser + screenshot
- `design_iterate` — Capture current browser state for iteration

### Project Index
- `index_project <dir>` — Index codebase for semantic search
- `index_search <query>` — Semantic search across indexed files

### Sub-Agents
- `agent_delegate <task>` — Delegate to best-matched specialist agent
- `agent_list` — List available agents

Available agents: frontend-designer, backend-architect, security-auditor, code-reviewer, debug-specialist, test-engineer, devops, researcher

### MCP Hub
- `mcp_route <server> <tool> <params>` — Route call to child MCP server
- `mcp_list_servers` — List connected MCP servers

### Monitor
- `monitor_status` — Session stats (tokens, cost, observations)
- `monitor_cost` — Cost breakdown by project

### Cron
- `cron_schedule <name> <expr> <cmd>` — Schedule recurring task
- `cron_list` — List scheduled tasks
- `cron_remove <id>` — Remove a task

### Skills
- `skill_run <name>` — Execute a skill by name or trigger phrase
- `skill_list` — List available skills
- `skill_install <path>` — Install a skill from a SKILL.md directory

Available skills: code-review, debug-loop, design-system, research, session-recap, security-audit, git-workflow, test-coverage

### Commands
- `command_run <name>` — Execute a slash command
- `command_list` — List available commands

Available commands: /generate-tests, /optimize-bundle, /security-audit, /explain-code, /refactor, /add-docs, /fix-lint, /generate-api-docs, /deploy-checklist, /session-recap

### Hooks
- `hook_trigger <name>` — Manually fire a hook
- `hook_list` — List active hooks

### Settings
- `settings_apply <preset>` — Apply a permission preset
- `settings_list` — List presets

Presets: full-access, read-only, ci-mode, security-audit, pair-programming

### Marketplace
- `marketplace_search <query>` — Search for components
- `marketplace_install <source>` — Install a component

### Workflows
- `workflow_run <name>` — Execute a multi-step workflow
- `workflow_list` — List workflows

Available workflows: ship-feature, bug-fix, code-review-cycle, new-project

